post_text: Kimberly Szymanski, a Campus Supervisor at Hamilton High School, was selected as the Faculty Focus Friday employee for high schools. Kim has been working tirelessly to keep students connected with their distance learning classrooms by making phone calls home. She has had to learn new skills in working with the re-engagement team and has adapted to this new role all with a smile on her face. We appreciate everything that Kim is doing to make Hamilton High a welcome and supportive home for our students and parents! #HUSDpremier

post_text: Bautista Creek's office staff (Terri, Lori, Lorraine, Ruby), Health Tech (Christi), Librarian (Melissa), and Assistant Principal (Amber) have been chosen as the Faculty Focus Friday employees for elementary schools. This team made the Data Validation process and Supply/Materials distribution a huge success. Parents and families had nothing but positive remarks about the system. They have also made the start-up of this extraordinary school year a welcoming one for everyone and assisted in troubleshooting technology issues, logging in concerns, and just plain frustrations. They have done it all with smiles on their faces (under their masks) and with a level of customer service that is second-to-none. Thank you all for your dedication, time, customer service, and support to improve the lives of Bautista Creek students, families, and community during the opening and throughout the year! #HUSDpremier

post_text: The SAFE and ZONE Expanded Learning Program is proud to recognize their Program Coach Team for Faculty Focus Friday for alternative sites. Jalisa Randle and Stephanie Russell work with and coach all 19 elementary and middle school sites with the SAFE/ZONE Program. They have provided amazing virtual professional development to the team to help them be prepared and confident for the new style of learning this year. We thank you both for going above and beyond to make the SAFE Virtual Tutoring and Enrichment Club Programs roll out a success. We appreciate you! #HUSDPremier

post_text: Timothy Poseley is this week’s Faculty Focus Friday employee for high schools. Mr. Poseley has worked as an Assistant Principal at Hemet High for the past two years and he has done an exceptional job. He was responsible for the design and implementation of their material distribution plan for students, he has supported classroom teachers and support staff with all things technology related, and is adept at assisting students with troubleshooting their technology needs. Mr. Posely has a tremendous sense of humor and is easy to work with. He has also created a variety of how-to videos to support parents, students, and staff. He has been a true asset to the Hemet High School community. Thank you Mr. Poseley for a job well done! #HUSDPremier

shared_text:
Dr. Christi Barrett
August 17 at 9:39 AM ·

The tradition continues! Every first day of school I walk classrooms, visit school sites, and see what support I can lend to our staff. This year, although kids are not on our campuses I decided to keep this tradition going. I cried when I went into our classrooms today. Not from sadness, but from the knowledge that our staff and students can overcome anything! Our teachers and kids are absolutely amazing! #HUSDpremier

Dear HUSD Families,

In light of the most recent California Department of Public Health order the District is anticipating opening the 2020-2021 school year via an online learning model. At the next regularly scheduled Board Meeting, Tuesday, July 21, the Governing Board will take action regarding the instructional model that HUSD will implement at the beginning of the new school year. Communication regarding our updated plan for the 2020-21 school year will be sent to families on Wednesday.

post_text:
Hello HUSD families,

This message is to inform you that HUSD has released its re-opening plan for the 2020-2021 school year. The document can be found on the district’s website at www.hemetusd.org. The document includes family survey results from the end of May and two options for students to receive instruction. Families can choose to enroll their children in traditional, on-campus, seat-based instruction, or a fully online instruction option. The document explains what families and students can expect with both options. In early July, all families will need to complete the revalidation process, and if you choose to enroll your child in the online instruction process you can fill out the application at that time.

As you may be aware, things change rapidly and we will, therefore, be sending two additional surveys before school starts in August. We understand that as orders are made or rescinded your decision to enroll your child in one of the options above may change and we want to make sure we are providing learning options that meet the needs of our families.

post_text: A huge shout out to our students in the SAFE After School Program. Despite school closures, SAFE students have continued to read and participate in the myON reading competition that ran from November 2019-May, 15, 2020. We would like to extend a special congratulations to Kadence Martinez (1st place) who spent 4,875 minutes reading 91 books equating to 4,319 pages; Joshlyn Banuela (2nd place) who spent 3,179 minutes reading 98 books equating to 4,651 pages, and Josiah Nava (3rd place) who spent 2,984 minutes reading 71 books equating to 1,646 pages. Great job to all of the 2,500 SAFE students that participated! #HUSDpremier

post_text: This week’s Faculty Focus Friday employee goes to Mr. Andy McGuire. Mr. McGuire is the Director of Purchasing who also oversees the Warehouse and the Print Shop. He has been instrumental in the organization of the meal and packet distribution since school closures. Mr. McGuire tirelessly works to ensure things go as smoothly as possible for our staff, students, and families. His work ethic, high energy, and can-do attitude make him a go-to employee when thinking outside the box and swift action is needed. Thank you, Mr. McGuire, for all that you do. You continue to help and make things easier for those in our organization and do it with humor that lifts the spirit of the team. #HUSDpremier

post_text: This week’s Faculty Focus Friday, we would like to highlight the work of Derek Rouch, Terri Patterson, and Ashley Yazarlou, the Educational-Technology Team for creating the HemetLearnsTogether.org website! In a short timeframe they were able to come together to create a user-friendly platform for our families that provides a wide range of meaningful resources for preschool through high school students, including support for English Learners and Special Education students. They also took the time to receive feedback from families as to their needs in terms of educational resources for their children and included them on the new website. They were mindful of the various situations our families may be in and included digital, television, and packet resources. They continue to add valuable resources and information for our families on the site, including social-emotional resources for our students and families. They continue to train and field questions from students, parents, and educators as HUSD moves from classroom to distance learning. Great job! #HUSDpremier

post_text:
After a little bit of a hiatus from our weekly Faculty Focus Friday posts, we are BACK! The first Faculty Focus Friday during school closures goes to our Nutrition Team, Hemet HusdNutrition! Since our school closures, they have been working tirelessly to make sure our students are fed. With the ever changing news and requirements, they have found solutions to keep production running while keeping safety of our students, families, and staff at the top of their priority. From March 16th (the first day of school closures) to April 3rd, Nutrition has prepared and helped distribute 172,028 meals! We are so thankful for our Nutrition team and all that they do!

*The photo was taken by staff at West Valley's meal distribution on April 3rd.

post_text:
Hello HUSD Families,

This communication is to provide you an update for our meal distributions. Starting next week (the week of April 13th) we will only serve meals on Wednesdays from 9:00 a.m.- 10:30 a.m. Children will receive five days worth of meals on Wednesdays. This new change reduces the number of times our students, families, and staff risk exposure. Families can also pick up weekly educational packets during meal distribution.

We want to remind our families that Riverside County Public Health has released an order for residents to wear face coverings when leaving the house. The face coverings do not need to be hospital grade, but need to cover the face and mouth. Examples can include bandanas, fabric masks, and neck gaiters. We ask our families to wear face coverings when visiting our meal distribution centers for your families’ safety and ours.

Thank you.

post_text:
This communication is to provide you with an update for educational enrichment resources for your child.
Educational Resources

At the start of our school closures, we provided educational enrichment resources on our website for students. Our administrators and teachers have been working diligently to launch a new website, www.hemetlearnstogether.org, that is more comprehensive and user-friendly for our students and families. This website will have digital resources, links to print weekly grade-level/subject activities packets, and sample daily schedules. This site will be updated weekly with new resources and materials for you and your child.

If you are unable to print these packets they can be picked up at meal distribution sites starting March 31st.

Although we are social distancing, it does not mean isolation, we are still Hemet Unified. We encourage students and families to share their HUSD Learning experience with us using #HemetLearnsTogether on social media. Please check back for the latest and follow Hemet Unified on Facebook and Twitter.

www.hemetlearnstogether.org,

post_text:
Hello HUSD Families,

This communication is to provide you an update for our meal distributions. Starting next week (the week of March 30th) we will only serve meals on Tuesdays, Wednesdays, and Fridays from 11:00 a.m.- 12:00 p.m. Children will receive two days worth of meals on Wednesdays and Fridays. Please see the photos below for a detailed breakdown.

In addition, the serving location for Rancho Viejo Middle School has been changed to Tahquitz High School, located next door. These changes go into effect next week. Families will receive their meals for Monday, March 30th on Friday, March 27th. We also want to remind families that HUSD will not be serving meals during the regularly scheduled Spring Break (April 6-10).

Thank you.

As you may be aware, HUSD staff are providing meals to students. Yesterday, we distributed a total of 12,000 meals. Due to the demand, we started running low of bags for our meals. These local grocery stores donated bags so that we could continue to serve the community. We are so proud to be a part of and serve our amazing communities!

post_text: Congratulations to Mr. Ahmed El-Sayad, known as Mr. El, the Faculty Focus Friday employee for high schools. Mr. El teaches social studies at West Valley High School, part of the team pioneering International Baccalaureate, and the boys’ soccer coach. He will be teaching the second-year IB social studies course which will focus on World War II. He works tirelessly to find ways to help students with their individual educational needs. Mr. El's larger than life personality makes him a highly recognizable figure no matter what role he is filling at the moment. He has a vast library of stories and experiences that make every interaction interesting and memorable. Thank you, Mr. El for all that you do for the students and the community! #HUSDpremier

post_text: Mrs. Candyce Lewis is the Faculty Focus Friday employee for elementary schools. Mrs. Lewis is the amazing school counselor at Jacob Wiens Elementary School. She truly believes that there is no better feeling than having a positive impact on a child. She understands that growing up can be tough, and school and what lies beyond can feel like a maze. Mrs. Lewis is an advocate for students and addresses their academic and social/emotional development and college and career readiness needs. To further engage students, Mrs. Lewis also works with several programs to help create a "connectedness culture" at Jacob Wiens Elementary. Mrs. Lewis provides students with Mindfulness sessions during their lunch, meets regularly with our crowned empowerment youth (Black Butterflies and Man Up), and leads our Peace Patrol, a student group. She is a school counselor who has the best interest of the students at the heart of everything she does and we are honored to recognize her contributions to the Jacob Wiens community. #HUSDpremier

post_text: Elias Lopez was chosen as the Faculty Focus Friday employee for middle schools. He has been a physical education teacher at Acacia Middle School, Home of Cougar Pride for seven years and has served as the Athletic Director for five years, Saturday School Coordinator and Soccer Head Coach for six years, and is currently serving his third year as Department Chair/Site Leader. One of the things Acacia staff appreciates most about Mr. Lopez is his management skills. He works with students during the soccer season, P.E. classes, and Saturday Schools, and it is impressive to see how students respond to him. He has a natural ability to lead and this is in great part to his relationship-building skills. He takes the time to know the students that he works with and treats every one of them with respect. Students under his supervision thrive and respect him because they know he cares. We are so fortunate to have Mr. Lopez as part of the Acacia team. Go Cougars!

post_text: YeVonne Ramirez was selected as the Faculty Focus Friday employee for elementary schools for her admirable work ethic and commitment to students. YeVonne is a SAI TK-3 teacher at Fruitvale Elementary School and an invaluable member to the Fruitvale Family. She serves as the SST Coordinator and is a member of the PBIS Tier II and III Teams. She works tirelessly to complete all assessments, IEP goals and services and still manages to go out of her way to assist staff and students in many capacities. She was extremely supportive with the preparation of a newly opened classroom and once jumped in as our Crossing Guard when the school was short-handed. Fruitvale staff said they are very blessed that YeVonne is a member of their Fruitvale family. She is devoted and dedicated to the education of the students she serves. Thank you for all that you do YeVonne!

post_text: Congratulations to Jennifer Hockman for being selected as the Faculty Focus Friday employee for our elementary schools. Mrs. Hockman teaches third grade and is also a grade-level lead at Cawston Elementary School. post_text: Cristen Yacovelli is the Faculty Focus Friday employee for Harmony Elementary School. Cris is a third grade teacher and has taught 17 years at Harmony. She started her career as a new teacher and helped to open Harmony in 2003. Cris is gifted and naturally meets all students at their social, emotional, and academic levels and takes them to even higher levels of achievement. She builds positive relationships with her students and carefully differentiates instruction based on students’ individual needs. Cris carefully focuses on the overall student and works with each child to achieve to their highest potential by teaching the “whole child”. This outstanding educator goes beyond academic development and strives to provide each one of her students overall success in life. Congratulations and thank you Cristen Yacovelli for everything you do! #HUSDpremier

text: We are pleased to celebrate Laura Hafner as the Faculty Focus employee for alternative sites. Laura is the Site Facilitator for the SAFE After School Program at Cottonwood K-8 School The words "No can do" are not in her vocabulary or mindset. She has worked tirelessly to support the Cottonwood families & students. She takes every challenge with a positive, compassionate & motivated attitude. She has worked really hard to provide a welcoming & engaging environment for students, which has resulted in improved attendance numbers in the Cottonwood SAFE program. Laura, we are super proud to call you a member of our SAFE team! Congrats and keep up the awesome work! #HUSDpremier
